    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "A/C capacitor removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the engine is hot, allow it to cool sufficiently before working on it."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Recovery of refrigerant",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R002698",
          "label": "Recovery of refrigerant",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. External temperature sensor removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000888",
          "label": "External temperature sensor removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Capacitor removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "885_5.0_jpn_11581007_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the harness clip (A). Disconnect the discharge hose (B). Disconnect the receiver pipe (C). Loosen the bolt (D). Remove the bolt (E) and remove the capacitor (F)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "After disconnecting, seal the connection immediately with a sealing plug or vinyl tape."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "After disconnecting, seal the connection immediately with a sealing plug or vinyl tape."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not damage radiator and capacitor cores."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Precautions for installation work"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "The O-ring at the pipe connection must be replaced with a new one, and compressor oil (SP-10) must be applied before installation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Vacuuming/leak testing/refrigerant sealing",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R002698",
          "label": "Vacuuming/leak testing/refrigerant sealing",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "After installation, perform vacuuming, leak test, and refrigerant sealing."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. performance test",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000907",
          "label": "performance test",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
